										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>TwelveLabs Raises $100 Million to Expand Video AI Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">TwelveLabs has raised $100 million to accelerate development of artificial intelligence platforms. The investment was co-led by NEA and NAVER Ventures. Amazon, Radical Ventures, Korea Investment Partners, Index Ventures, Quadrille Capital and Red Bull Ventures also participated.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round pushes TwelveLabs’ fundraising total to close to $150 million. The company will use the cash to invest in research, product development and international growth, with new offices set to open in New York and London as well as existing hubs in San Francisco and Seoul.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">TwelveLabs was founded in 2021 and builds AI models that analyze existing video content, rather than producing new video. It says this empowers organisations to discover meaningful information in massive video libraries that are currently cumbersome to navigate.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Models Turn Raw Video into Searchable Intelligence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike AI companies focused on video generation, TwelveLabs concentrates on helping organisations understand existing footage. Its technology is designed for industries with large video archives, including media, security, advertising, sport and government.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s Marengo model converts speech, sounds, motion and visual events into searchable information. A second model, Pegasus, organises that information into structured data capable of identifying relationships, timelines and events across lengthy recordings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Jae Lee said the company&#8217;s long-term advantage comes from building an intelligence layer that extracts meaningful knowledge from video rather than relying solely on increasingly commoditised AI models.</span></p>
<h2><b>Amazon Strengthens Strategic Partnership</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203323" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203323" class="size-full wp-image-203323" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/TwelveLabs-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI models deployed on hyperscale cloud infrastructure, showing strategic cloud partnerships, advanced AI accelerators, and enterprise-scale multimodal computing. " width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203323" class="wp-caption-text">Strategic cloud partnerships are becoming a key driver of AI infrastructure growth, combining long-term cloud collaboration, optimized AI hardware, and enterprise deployment platforms to accelerate next-generation artificial intelligence development. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of the most significant developments from the funding round extends beyond the investment itself. Amazon has formalised Amazon Web Services as TwelveLabs&#8217; preferred cloud provider following its participation in the latest financing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The partnership means future AI models will be optimised for AWS Trainium chips before broader deployment. Both Marengo and Pegasus are already available through Amazon Bedrock as well as TwelveLabs&#8217; own application programming interface.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry observers increasingly view these investments as strategic cloud partnerships rather than simple venture capital transactions. Cloud providers secure long-term infrastructure customers while supporting advanced AI computing workloads.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NAVER Ventures also marked an important milestone through the investment. The firm launched its Silicon Valley venture arm during 2025, making TwelveLabs its first portfolio company and later co-leading this latest funding round.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-systems-raises-1-2b-series-d-to-expand-defence-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Systems Raises $1.2B Series D to Expand Defence AI</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Demand Drives Video Intelligence Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">TwelveLabs has expanded rapidly over the past year. Its workforce has grown from fewer than 60 employees to around 178 people. The company now supports customers across media, entertainment, government, security and enterprise sectors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Demand for AI-powered video search continues to increase as organisations seek practical applications beyond content generation.Businesses hold extensive video </span><a href="https://www.ica.org/discover-archives/what-are-archives/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">archives</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> with valuable operational information inaccessible through traditional search tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will support continued research in San Francisco and Seoul while expanding customer operations in Europe and North America. The company also expects to strengthen its platform for enterprise customers requiring advanced video analysis at scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As artificial intelligence adoption accelerates, TwelveLabs is pursuing a different strategy from companies building video generation tools. It helps organisations transform video into searchable intelligence supporting decision-making and operational efficiency.</span></p>
