					<description><![CDATA[<p>LinqAlpha Raises Series A to Scale Institutional AI Platform LinqAlpha has raised $22 million in a Series A funding round to accelerate the growth of its artificial intelligence platform for</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/linqalpha-raises-22-million-series-a-to-expand-ai-market-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal">LinqAlpha Raises $22 Million Series A to Expand AI Market Intelligence</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>LinqAlpha Raises Series A to Scale Institutional AI Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LinqAlpha has raised $22 million in a Series A funding round to accelerate the growth of its artificial intelligence platform for institutional investors. The round was anchored by AVP, Atinum Investment, and GFT Ventures. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Several strategic financial institutions and venture platforms across Asia, Europe, and the United States also participated. The New York-based company develops what it describes as an Alpha Intelligence Layer for global public markets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its platform helps investment professionals process complex market information through specialised AI agents. The latest funding increases LinqAlpha&#8217;s total capital raised to approximately $28.6 million.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2022 by Jacob Choi, Subeen Pang, Jin Kim, and Hojun Choi, the company combines financial expertise with artificial intelligence research. The founding team includes former Goldman Sachs analysts alongside MIT computer science graduates.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Agents Aim to Improve Investment Research</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Public markets have become increasingly interconnected. Investors now monitor earnings reports, policy developments, supply chain events, credit markets, and social media signals simultaneously. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LinqAlpha believes traditional research methods struggle to keep pace with this growing volume of information. Its platform allows investment teams to deploy AI agents trained on their own research history instead of relying on generic language models. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They then connect new market developments with previous investment ideas to generate relevant insights. He added that the competitive advantage comes from identifying market-moving signals before they become widely recognised.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Client Base Supports Expansion Plans</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203315" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203315" class="size-full wp-image-203315" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/LinqAlpha-2.png" alt="Illustration of an AI investment intelligence platform connecting global financial institutions through real-time market analysis, research automation, and multi-asset investment strategies. " width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203315" class="wp-caption-text">Growing adoption among financial institutions is accelerating the expansion of AI-powered investment intelligence, enabling research, trading, and portfolio teams to analyse diverse market data and support faster, more informed decision-making across global markets. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LinqAlpha says more than 70 financial institutions currently use its platform. Customers include research, </span><a href="https://www.ig.com/en/trading-need-to-knows/what-is-trading" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">trading</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and sales teams at major investment banks. Buy-side clients also include Causeway Capital Management LLC and Schonfeld Strategic Advisors LLC. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company originally launched in Cambridge, Massachusetts. It later operated between South Korea and the United States before establishing its headquarters in New York. During that period, the business also completed two rebrands before adopting the LinqAlpha name.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding will help the company expand its international workforce. Management also plans to strengthen integrations with market and alternative datasets. Additional investment will support deployment across equities, macro, credit, and multi-asset investment strategies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Jacob Choi, co-founder and co-chief executive officer, said the platform is designed to become an extension of each investment team&#8217;s thinking by continuously learning from previous research and market feedback.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/spacex-secures-6-3b-compute-deal-with-reflection-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">SpaceX Secures $6.3B Compute Deal With Reflection AI</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Competition Intensifies Across Financial AI</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">LinqAlpha enters a competitive market for artificial intelligence research platforms. Demand continues to grow as investment firms seek faster analysis without sacrificing proprietary insights.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to AVP General Partner Manish Agarwal, many AI products focus on automating routine work or accelerating information retrieval. He believes LinqAlpha helps investors identify differentiated investment ideas through context-driven intelligence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Competition remains significant. Larger AI research providers have secured substantially more funding over recent years. However, LinqAlpha argues its specialised approach offers a stronger fit for institutional investors seeking customised analysis rather than standard AI outputs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry forecasts also suggest continued expansion across financial AI. Growing adoption among banks, insurers, and asset managers is expected to attract further investment into companies developing specialised enterprise AI platforms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest funding provides LinqAlpha with additional resources to strengthen its technology and expand internationally. Its long-term success will likely depend on demonstrating measurable value for institutional clients operating in increasingly complex global markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/linqalpha-raises-22-million-series-a-to-expand-ai-market-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal">LinqAlpha Raises $22 Million Series A to Expand AI Market Intelligence</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
