<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/together-ai-raises-800m-series-c-open-source-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Together AI Raises $800M At $8.3B Valuation to Scale Cheaper Open-Source Models</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Even as artificial intelligence continues to change a lot in the world, the technology is also evolving. We’re seeing a move from restrictive and expensive closed-source AI models to customizable and affordable open-source alternatives. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Together AI is one of the names feeding into this massive market shift. To scale its open-source models, the AI infrastructure pioneer has just </span><a href="https://www.together.ai/blog/announcing-our-series-c" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">announced</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> a staggering $800 million in Series C funding raise. Together AI raises $800m, propelling its valuation to a whopping $8.3 billion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This marks a meteoric rise from its $3.3 billion valuation just over a year ago. Together AI’s Series C funding was led by Aramco Ventures and positions the company to aggressively challenge closed-ecosystem tech giants.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Driving Down the Massive Cost of AI Compute</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203284" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203284" class="size-large wp-image-203284" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/TogetherAI-1024x571.jpg" alt="Together AI team of founders featuring Vipul Ved Prakash, Percy Liang, and Ce Zhang." width="1024" height="571" /><p id="caption-attachment-203284" class="wp-caption-text">Founders. Image Credit: Together AI</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of the major complaints surrounding AI has been the enormous computing power it consumes. For companies building and relying on AI, they usually get astronomical bills. Together AI is tackling this power problem head-on. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup provides a dedicated cloud infrastructure layer that allows developers to train and deploy open-source models seamlessly. The primary draw for businesses is pure cost efficiency. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the company, moving workloads to its platform can cut inference costs significantly. In fact, one client reported a massive sixfold reduction in expenses. This financial relief makes high-performance AI highly accessible to everyday companies rather than just tech elites.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/leapxpert-raises-180m-to-unlock-insights-from-work-chats/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>LeapXpert Raises $180M to Unlock Insights From Work Chats</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Surging Enterprise Demand for Open-Source Technology</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Open-source AI has transformed from a developer hobby into a core enterprise strategy. Over the past twelve months, the industry’s usage of open-source models has tripled. Businesses love the freedom to customize these models without being locked into a single vendor’s ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Together AI is directly capitalizing on this momentum. The company revealed that its annual bookings recently topped $1.15 billion. It now services thousands of paying corporate customers who are actively ditching closed AI setups. The goal is to make intelligence abundant and cheap for everyone.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Aggressive Global Infrastructure Expansion Ahead</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Building a heavy-duty AI cloud requires physical infrastructure to match the software ambition. Together AI will use the $800 million injection to scale its hardware footprint and expand product features. On top of the fresh equity, CEO Vipul Ved Prakash announced a major operational win. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has secured commitments for over </span><a href="https://www.together.ai/blog/announcing-our-series-c" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">500 megawatts</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> of dedicated compute capacity. This massive energy and hardware pool will be capitalized independently by strategic investors. This guarantees that Together AI can effortlessly support its skyrocketing enterprise demand.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding milestone highlights a broader philosophical shift in Silicon Valley and beyond. Closed platforms have held the dominant keys to AI power for years. Now, decentralized and open-source ecosystems are rapidly closing the capability gap.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/dominion-dynamics-raises-139m-cad-for-arctic-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Dominion Dynamics Raises $139M CAD for Arctic Expansion</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/together-ai-raises-800m-series-c-open-source-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Together AI Raises $800M At $8.3B Valuation to Scale Cheaper Open-Source Models</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
