</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">What to Do if the Binance Referral Code Doesn’t Work?</span></h2>
<p>Most failures come down to mistyping the code, entering it after signup, or being in a restricted region. The code can&#8217;t be added or changed once the account exists, so double-check it before hitting Create Account. Here&#8217;s what usually causes it:</p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Wrong typing.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Code is <strong>VB2025</strong>. Nothing else. If you add a space, or lowercase weirdly, it won’t work.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Too late.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> You only enter a Binance referral code at signup. Once the account is created, that’s it. Can’t add it later.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Location issues.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Some countries can’t use referral bonuses at all. UK, Nigeria, Turkey, Japan, Hong Kong — blocked. If you live there, the code won’t unlock anything.</span></li>
